.Sh NAME
.Nm freecell
.Nd patience game
.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl d Ar delay
.Op Fl n Ar game
.
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a terminal FreeCell patience game.
The arguments are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl d Ar delay
Set the delay in milliseconds
between queued moves.
The default is 50.
.It Fl n Ar game
Select the game number to play.
.El
.
.Pp
Moves are performed
by typing a sequence of two keys.
To automatically move a card
to a free cell,
type the same key twice.
The keys are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic Escape
Cancel a pending move.
.It Ic u , Backspace
Undo the previous move.
.It Ic 1 , 2 , 3 , 4
Select the cells.
.It Ic q , w , e , r , a , s , d , f
Select the tableau cascades.
.It Ic _ , Space
Manually move
the selected card
to the foundations.
.It Ic Shift
Move a single card
to an empty tableau cascade.
.El
